13 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the title, enacting clause, and entire bill
and insert:
14
15
16 "An Act relating to teachers; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-101.3, which relates to definitions for
17 teachers; modifying definition for career teacher for
evaluation purposes; and providing an effective date.
18
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-101.3, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1317 Page 1

1 Section 6-101.3. As used in Section 6-101 et seq. of this
2 title:
3 1. "Administrator" means a duly certified person who devotes a
4 majority of time to service as a superintendent, elementary
5 superintendent, principal, supervisor, vice principal or in any
6 other administrative or supervisory capacity in the school district;
7 2. "Dismissal" means the discontinuance of the teaching service
8 of an administrator or teacher during the term of a written
9 contract, as provided by law;
10 3. "Nonreemployment" means the nonrenewal of the contract of an
11 administrator or teacher upon expiration of the contract;
12 4. "Career teacher" means a teacher who:
13 a. is employed by a school district prior to the 2017-
14 2018 school year and has completed three (3) or more
15 consecutive complete school years as a teacher in one
16 school district under a written continuing or
17 temporary teaching contract, or
18 b. is employed for the first time by a school district
19 under a written continuing or temporary teaching
20 contract during the 2017-2018 school year and
21 thereafter, and:
22 (1) has completed three (3) consecutive complete
23 school years as a teacher in one school district
24 under a written continuing or temporary teaching
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1317 Page 2

1 contract and has achieved a district evaluation
2 rating of "superior" as measured pursuant to the
3 TLE as set forth in Section 6-101.16 of this
4 title for at least two (2) of the three (3)
5 school years,
6 (2) has completed four (4) consecutive complete
7 school years as a teacher in one school district
8 under a written continuing or temporary teaching
9 contract, has averaged a district evaluation
10 rating of at least "effective" as measured
11 pursuant to the TLE for the four-year period, and
12 has received district evaluation ratings of at
13 least "effective" for the last two (2) years of
14 the four-year period, or
15 (3) has completed four (4) or more consecutive
16 complete school years in one school district
17 under a written continuing or temporary teaching
18 contract and has not met the requirements of
19 subparagraph a or b of this paragraph, only if
20 the principal of the school at which the teacher
21 is employed submits a petition to the
22 superintendent of the school district requesting
23 that the teacher be granted career status, the
24 superintendent agrees with the petition, and the
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1317 Page 3

1 school district board of education approves the
2 petition. The principal shall specify in the
3 petition the underlying facts supporting the
4 granting of career status to the teacher, or
5 c. after meeting the requirements of subparagraph a or b
6 of this paragraph in one school district, is employed
7 by another school district under a written continuing
8 or temporary teaching contract and the board of
9 education of the school district has approved the
10 granting of career status to the teacher. Status as a
11 career teacher pursuant to this paragraph shall be for
12 evaluation purposes only;
13 5. "Teacher hearing" means the hearing before a school district
14 board of education after a recommendation for dismissal or
15 nonreemployment of a teacher has been made but before any final
16 action is taken on the recommendation, held for the purpose of
17 affording the teacher all rights guaranteed by the United States
18 Constitution and the Constitution of Oklahoma under circumstances
19 and for enabling the board to determine whether to approve or
20 disapprove the recommendation;
21 6. "Probationary teacher" means a teacher who:
22 a. is employed by a school district prior to the 2017-
23 2018 school year and has completed fewer than three
24 (3) consecutive complete school years as a teacher in
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1317 Page 4

1 one school district under a written teaching contract,
2 or
3 b. is employed for the first time by a school district
4 under a written teaching contract during the 2017-2018
5 school year and thereafter and has not met the
6 requirements for career teacher as provided in
7 paragraph 4 of this section;
8 7. "Suspension" or "suspended" means the temporary
9 discontinuance of the services of an administrator or teacher, as
10 provided by law;
11 8. "Teacher" means a person defined as a teacher in Section 1-
12 116 of this title; and
13 9. "District evaluation rating" means the rating issued based
14 on the components of the TLE as set forth in subsection B of Section
15 6-101.16 of this title.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026."
